  "texts": [
    "Database search and retrieval: the next step is to systematically search the current academic literature for relevant papers.",
    "This is done by brainstorming and defining appropriate keywords that are directly related to the research topic, without claiming to be exhaustive.",
    "Variations of the keywords are then added to the pool to account for differences in spelling.",
    "Finally, the keywords are divided into two groups and linked within each group using the logical operator OR, while both groups are linked together using the logical operator AND.",
    "The resulting search string is then used in scientific databases such as Ebsco Host, Elsevier, Emerald, Google Scholar, Springer Link, Web of Science, and Wiley Online."
  ],
